<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900907-0030</DOCNO><DOCID>900907-0030.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- USX Corp.:   Marathon Oil Unit to Install   Platform in Gulf of Mexico</HL><DATE>09/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   X AHC LLX OKCPZ</CO><IN>OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><LP>   Marathon Oil Co., a unit of Pittsburgh-based USX Corp.,said it will install a drilling and production platform inthe Gulf of Mexico.   The platform, located at a site called South Pass Block86, will be used to develop more than 50 million equivalentbarrels of hydrocarbon liquids discovered in 1988. The welltested at a rate of 9.6 million cubic feet of gas per day and1,270 barrels of condensate per day.</LP><TEXT>   The offshore Louisiana field was further delineated by asecond well, which tested at a rate of 3,666 barrels of oilper day and 4.3 million cubic feet of gas per day.   The platform is being designed to handle production of20,000 barrels of oil per day, with an initial gas handlingcapacity of 100 million cubic feet per day. Installation isset for early 1992.   Other partners in the development are Amerada Hess Corp.,the Louisiana Land andamp; Exploration Co. and OKC LimitedPartnership. Each owns 25% of South Pass Block 86.</TEXT></DOC>